BUGS / TODO (historical list from UNINETT; many items addressed in this tree)

Addressed in current source:
- IPv6 hop limit / “TTL” on receive: use IPV6_RECVHOPLIMIT + recvmsg ancillary data (IPV6_HOPLIMIT cmsg); print as `hops=N` like IPv4 `ttl=`.
- Kernel timestamps (-k): SO_TIMESTAMP + recvmsg SCM_TIMESTAMP used for receive-side time when computing RTT (with -k).
- Long-run DNS failures: hosts that fail getaddrinfo at startup stay in the list; resolution is retried every RESOLVE_RETRY_SEC (30s) when their turn comes in the round-robin. PING line shows “DNS unresolved, will retry”. Main loop sleeps if no raw sockets exist yet.
- stdin hostname vs DNS: PING line shows `PING <stdin> [canonical]: … to <addr>` when ai_canonname is present; hostnameresolv[] holds canonical name.
- Duplicate replies: dupcheck() keyed by (host_index << 16) | seq; prints “(DUP!)” and skips updating stats.
- pr_pack6: hnum bounds check uses `>= nhosts` (was `> nhosts`).

Still open / optional:
- Further polish of display format for resolved vs user-supplied names.
- Packed output mode could include IPv6 hop count for parity with IPv4 ttl field.
- Per-host dupcheck ring size is fixed at 100 (tunable constant).

See Changelog / git history for portability work (Linux, macOS, Makefile, README).
